    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ee86cdd4_606247d7",
        "filename": "android/base/ipc/SerialLine.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 30,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-28T18:16:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Well, I tried to do it that way first, but here are two issues I found:\n1. There\u0027s no good way to wrap it under C interface which allows later handler changes. And current char device works this way\n2. If I understand it correctly, add_handlers() is called when everything is set up and ready, which is quite often much later than the original object creation. It\u0027s like a \u0027on-off switch\u0027 for the communication channel.\n\nAnd there\u0027s a non-issue but small annoyance - every single custom set of handlers would require its own subclass, with constructor and everything - it feels like an overkill to me",
      "parentUuid": "0eb5e1d9_3deafbb0",
      "revId": "6e91c884e0d90e27bbd7ae44c0878e0201f5b6d5",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
